	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/MM_TV_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff"><b>The UK Today</b></font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Today saw the launch of the new daily newspaper 'The UK Today'. According to the paper's editor, Charles Moody, 'The UK Today' is aimed at a younger twenty-something <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q1" type="droptarget" /></font> and is expected to reach an average <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q2" type="droptarget" /></font> of 200,000 in its first year. </font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Although the paper is <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q3" type="droptarget" /></font> in format, Moody was quick to point out that it will have as much serious news as any of the <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q4" type="droptarget" /></font>. One of its most striking features is its highly unusual <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q5" type="droptarget" /></font>. Articles aren't laid out in <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q6" type="droptarget" /></font> but in boxes, each accompanied by a colour photograph. </font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">You'll find all the usual sections - national and international news, financial news, arts and entertainment, sport and, of course, <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q7" type="droptarget" />&#160;</font>advertisements. </font></p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">So, what's in today's <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q8" type="droptarget" /></font>? Well, on the <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q9" type="droptarget" /></font>, under the eye-catching banner <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q10" type="droptarget" /></font> 'More hot air?' is an in-depth <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q11" type="droptarget" /></font> on the outcomes of this week's international summit meeting on global warming. Well worth a read!</font></p><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p>
